article.headline: Alabama A&M 77, Alcorn State 63
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. (AP) -- Obie Trotter had 21 points, Marcus Young added 19 and Alabama A&M beat Alcorn State 77-63 on Saturday night. Trotter was 9-of-15 from the field, Young made 11-of-12 free throws and the first-place Bulldogs (13-10, 10-3 Southwestern Athletic Conference) won for the eighth time in nine games. Marcus Jones added 13 points and Joseph Martin had 12 rebounds for Alabama A&M. Delvin Thompson led Alcorn State (5-20, 4-10) with 24 points, but was just 9-of-22 from the field. Juan Wyatt added 10 points and 12 rebounds for the Braves. Alcorn State has lost five straight and eight of nine. The Braves were just 3-of-21 from 3-point range, had 23 turnovers and allowed Alabama A&M to shoot 44 percent from the field in the second half.
